column8:
キルティング生地
Spring day
北欧テイストのデザインが大人気のシリーズです。 こちらの生地は「spring day（スプリングデイ）」。白地に淡い色合いで並ぶ 黄色いバラたちが、上品でかわいいコットンのキルティング生地です。

生産工場の変更により、前回ロットとは糸や裏布などの一部仕様が異なります。
あらかじめご了承の上お買い求めください。





本商品のキルトの縫い目のパターンは細長いダイヤ形です。
一部イメージ画像とは縫い目のパターンが異なります。ご了承の上お買い求めください。


キルティング裏地部分に皺がよることがございます。
製造状避けられないものですので、あらかじめご了承の上お買い求めください。

コットンフランネル生地
blooming
北欧テイストのフラワー模様が人気のシリーズです。
こちらの生地は「blooming（ブルーミング）」、 明るいグレーに白い花が並ぶ、上品で可愛いデザインです。

こちらの生地は肌触りの柔らかい片面起毛のコットンフランネル生地です。 コットン生地の表面のみを起毛させた暖かみのある素材で、 クッションカバーやブランケット、ネックウォーマーなどにおすすめです。

──【メーカーカタログより】──
Being a quilter and an Army Wife, I'm always looking for military themed fabric, especially after my husband deployed to Afghanistan two years ago. Unfortunately, I have never found anything that was "rustic" enough for my soldier. I wanted a line that was traditional and relevant, but NOT novelty. It's a good thing I work for a fabric company! I've always loved a burlap texture, and this fabric brings in that look without the rough feel. The silhouettes are powerful and strong. The patches provide authenticity. The words, hopefully, invoke patriotism. It was important to us that we recognize the sacrifices that military families make. Families serve the nation too. Charities that assist wounded and homeless veterans are honorable and important, but their causes get a fair amount of attention. Military families, on the other hand, also face down adversity and endure hardships; yet all too often their troubles go unnoticed. Sometimes they just need a little hand-up, instead of a hand-out. Therefore, we have chosen USA Cares (www.usacares.org) as this line's recipient for charitable contributions. USA Cares exists to help military families bear the burdens of their service in a time of need. This fabric line is for those Soldiers, Sailors, Airmen, and Marines who must miss holidays, birthdays, and family moments in far-away distant lands. It is for the family members who keep the house running while their husband, wife, son or daughter is away. It is for the children who dearly miss their deployed parent, brother, sister, uncle, or aunt. In short, this fabric...
